text: i joined aws straight out of university
through the tecu graduate program
i studied applied physics in the
netherlands and graduated with a
specialization in quantum hardware
research
i've always had a very wide set of
interests like running my university's
first crowdfunding platform
studying abroad in singapore and taking
management consulting courses
when looking for my first job i knew i
wanted to work for a company that could
satisfy all my interests and ambitions
which is not easy it is for this reason
that i started looking at aws
as i knew they provided a wide range of
modern technologies
were focused on driving customer value
and also had an international scope
as i really wanted to work abroad today
i'm a partner solution architect working
with aws partners to build their
practices from a business and a
technical perspective
i help them do this through strategy
meetings offer design
running joint marketing campaigns
organizing technical workshops and also
through identifying and onboarding these
partners to the aws partner network the
apn
outside of my day to day i'd like to be
a spokesperson for women in technology
and participate in hiring activities and
panel discussions to encourage more
women to go into i.t
i've experienced first hand that if you
think big and advice for action
everything is possible at aws no matter
your role or seniority
